propertyDescriptor.label: Business Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the business perspective using a score 0-100. This includes all non-technical requirements such as regulatory compliance, vendors support or security and is calculated as a weighted average of the compliance in these individual areas.

propertyDescriptor.label: Technical Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the technical perspective using a score 0-100. This includes all requirements such as infrastructure/operating environment compatibility and is calculated as a weighted average of the compliance in these individual areas.

propertyDescriptor.label: Financial Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the financial perspective using a score 0-100. An entity that pays off to change the deployment style the most has score 100, other entities have the score proportional to the savings that can be reached by their change of deployment style (compared to the entity with score 100). Entities where savings are not achievable have score 0.

propertyDescriptor.label: Technical Alignment Information Quality
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines the percentage ratio of answers that provide real information (The ratio of all answers except "Don't know", "Cannot be determined" and the number of all answers)

propertyDescriptor.label: Business Alignnment Information Quality
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines the percentage ratio of answers that provide real information (The ratio of all answers except "Don't know", "Cannot be determined" and the number of all answers)

propertyDescriptor.label: Financial Alignment Information Quality
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines the percentage ratio of answers that provide real information (The ratio of all answers except "Don't know", "Cannot be determined" and the number of all answers)

propertyDescriptor.label: Regulatory Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the regulatory/compliance perspective using a score 0-100. This includes requirements implied by law/government.

propertyDescriptor.label: Vendor Support Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the application vendor perspective using a score 0-100. This means whether the vendor is supporting cloud/virtual machine deployment.

propertyDescriptor.label: Security Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the security perspective using a score 0-100. This means whether communication and storage of the application are encrypted.

propertyDescriptor.label: Service Availability Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the application availability perspective using a score 0-100. This means how tolerant users are to service outages, increased latency, etc.

propertyDescriptor.label: Workload Variability Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the application workload perspective using a score 0-100. This means whether there are peaks in usage during weekly holidays and so on.

propertyDescriptor.label: Geography Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from the application hosting location perspective using a score 0-100. This means whether there are strict requirements on the location where the application is hosted due to legal/licence reasons.

propertyDescriptor.label: Architecture Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from a technical point of view using a score 0-100. This includes use of proper development means, such as using C++ compiled binaries versus applications compiled into the byte code. Such applications are easier to migrate between operating systems and similar metrics.

propertyDescriptor.label: Internet Access Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from its Internet access requirements point of view using a score 0-100. This includes use of standard protocols and bandwith requirements.

propertyDescriptor.label: HP CSA Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible deployment using HP Cloud Service Automation/HP Codar using a score 0-100.

propertyDescriptor.label: Performance Requirements Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from technical point of view using a score 0-100. This includes the hardware requirements of the application.

propertyDescriptor.label: Infrastructure Requirements Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment from an infrastructure point of view using a score 0-100. This includes dependencies on special hardware and software that are difficult to move to the cloud for example.

propertyDescriptor.label: Cloud Operating Model Alignment
propertyDescriptor.description: Defines alignment of this entity with possible cloud deployment using a score 0-100. This includes meeting requirements to be met when an application is running in a cloud.

propertyDescriptor.label: Implications

It will often be apparent that current systems, standards, or practices would be incongruent with the principle upon adoption. The impact to the business and consequences of adopting a principle should be clearly stated. The reader should readily discern the answer to "How does this affect me?" It is important not to oversimplify, trivialize, or judge the merit of the impact. Some of the implications will be identified as potential impacts only, and may be speculative rather than fully analyzed.
